    <h1>CHOOSE YOUR WORK&#xAD;OUTS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201125/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-25"><time>2020-11-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | LIVING WELL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Driven by a de­sire to ful­fil at least one Well­ness Chal­lenge, I pushed my­self to do more.</p>
    <p>Well­ness Chal­lenges on the Lu­miHealth app gen­er­ally don’t limit you to spe­cific work­outs. You have free rein to choose any phys­i­cal ac­tiv­ity you like. I went for a hike at Lower Peirce Reser­voir Park, and logged my jour­ney through it. I even en­joyed it enough to go well be­yond the 15-minute time limit I was given to com­plete my Well­ness Chal­lenge.</p>
    <p>What I ap­pre­ci­ate about Lu­miHealth is that it’s all about help­ing you make grad­ual changes in your life­style, one step at a time. Even if you are a first-time health app user like my­self, Lu­miHealth’s in­tu­itive in­ter­face eases you through the process. Some would say you barely have to break a sweat.</p>

